                    <desc>The term nibandhana (bshad sbyar) in this context, appears to refer to a very specific style of commentary, in which descriptive summaries of passages in a
            root text are provided with only minimal reference to the source (e.g. “Then one verse indicates the difficulties of realizing that”; de nas tshigs su bcad pa gcig gis de rtogs par dka' ba
            bstan to). The best way to render the term nibandhana (bshad sbyar) in English is unclear, although the contents of the text would seems to suggest rendering the title as "A Skeleton Key
            to 'The Compendium of the Essence of Exalted Wisdom'.”</desc>
